<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <title><%= pageTitle %> | MyTaxCalcs</title>
  <meta name="description" content="Use our free income tax calculator to estimate federal taxable income, tax owed, refund, effective tax rate, and marginal tax rate.">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/style.css">
<script async src="https://pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js?client=ca-pub-5193834725888549"
     crossorigin="anonymous"></script>
</head>
<body>
  <header class="small-header">
    <nav class="nav">
      <a href="/" class="logo">MyTaxCalcs</a>
      <div>
        <a href="/income-tax-calculator">Income Tax</a>
        <a href="/contact">Contact</a>
      </div>
    </nav>
  </header>

  <main class="container two-column">
    <section class="card">
      <h1>Free Income Tax Calculator</h1>
      <p>Estimate your federal income tax, taxable income, refund, or amount owed.</p>

      <form method="POST" action="/income-tax-calculator" class="form">
        <label>
          Gross annual income
          <input type="number" name="grossIncome" value="<%= form.grossIncome || '' %>" placeholder="85000" required>
        </label>

        <label>
          Filing status
          <select name="filingStatus">
            <option value="single">Single</option>
            <option value="marriedJoint">Married Filing Jointly</option>
            <option value="marriedSeparate">Married Filing Separately</option>
            <option value="headHousehold">Head of Household</option>
          </select>
        </label>

        <label>
          Deduction type
          <select name="deductionType">
            <option value="standard">Standard deduction</option>
            <option value="itemized">Itemized deduction</option>
          </select>
        </label>

        <label>
          Itemized deduction amount
          <input type="number" name="itemizedDeduction" value="<%= form.itemizedDeduction || '' %>" placeholder="0">
        </label>

        <label>
          Federal tax withheld
          <input type="number" name="federalWithheld" value="<%= form.federalWithheld || '' %>" placeholder="12000">
        </label>

        <label>
          Tax credits
          <input type="number" name="taxCredits" value="<%= form.taxCredits || '' %>" placeholder="0">
        </label>

        <button type="submit">Calculate Tax Estimate</button>
      </form>
    </section>

    <section class="card">
      <h2>Estimated Results</h2>

      <% if (!result) { %>
        <p class="muted">Enter your information to see your tax estimate.</p>
      <% } else { %>
        <div class="results">
          <p><span>Gross income:</span> <strong>$<%= Math.round(result.grossIncome).toLocaleString() %></strong></p>
          <p><span>Deduction:</span> <strong>$<%= Math.round(result.deduction).toLocaleString() %></strong></p>
          <p><span>Taxable income:</span> <strong>$<%= Math.round(result.taxableIncome).toLocaleString() %></strong></p>
          <p><span>Federal tax after credits:</span> <strong>$<%= Math.round(result.federalTaxAfterCredits).toLocaleString() %></strong></p>
          <p><span>Federal tax withheld:</span> <strong>$<%= Math.round(result.federalWithheld).toLocaleString() %></strong></p>

          <% if (result.refundOrOwed >= 0) { %>
            <p><span>Estimated refund:</span> <strong>$<%= Math.round(result.refundOrOwed).toLocaleString() %></strong></p>
          <% } else { %>
            <p><span>Estimated amount owed:</span> <strong>$<%= Math.abs(Math.round(result.refundOrOwed)).toLocaleString() %></strong></p>
          <% } %>

          <p><span>Effective tax rate:</span> <strong><%= (result.effectiveTaxRate * 100).toFixed(1) %>%</strong></p>
          <p><span>Marginal tax rate:</span> <strong><%= (result.marginalRate * 100).toFixed(1) %>%</strong></p>
        </div>
      <% } %>

      <p class="disclaimer">Estimate only. Not tax, legal, accounting, or financial advice.</p>
    </section>
  </main>

  <section class="container content seo-content">
  <p class="eyebrow dark">Income Tax Calculator Guide</p>
  <h2>How this income tax calculator works</h2>
  <p>
    This income tax calculator estimates federal income tax by using your gross income,
    filing status, deduction choice, federal withholding, and tax credits. It then estimates
    taxable income, federal tax after credits, effective tax rate, marginal tax rate, and
    whether you may receive a refund or owe additional federal tax.
  </p>

  <div class="seo-grid">
    <div class="seo-mini-card">
      <h3>What it includes</h3>
      <p>
        The calculator includes gross income, standard or itemized deductions, filing status,
        federal withholding, and tax credits entered by the user.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="seo-mini-card">
      <h3>What it estimates</h3>
      <p>
        Results include taxable income, estimated federal tax, refund or amount owed,
        effective tax rate, and marginal tax rate.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="seo-mini-card">
      <h3>What it does not include</h3>
      <p>
        The calculator does not include every tax credit, phaseout, local tax, alternative
        minimum tax, Medicare surtax, or special tax situation.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2>Frequently asked questions</h2>

  <div class="faq-list">
    <div class="faq-item">
      <h3>Is this income tax calculator exact?</h3>
      <p>
        No. This calculator provides an estimate only. Your actual tax result may be different
        based on credits, deductions, dependents, retirement contributions, business income,
        state taxes, and other tax rules.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <h3>What is taxable income?</h3>
      <p>
        Taxable income is generally the amount of income left after subtracting deductions
        from gross income. This calculator estimates taxable income based on the deduction
        option you select.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <h3>What is the difference between marginal and effective tax rate?</h3>
      <p>
        A marginal tax rate is the rate applied to the last portion of taxable income.
        An effective tax rate is the estimated total federal tax divided by gross income.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <h3>Does this calculator include state income tax?</h3>
      <p>
        This page focuses on federal income tax. You can use the state calculator pages
        for state-specific tax information and state income tax estimates as those formulas
        are added.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <h3>Should I use standard or itemized deductions?</h3>
      <p>
        Many taxpayers use the standard deduction, but some may itemize if their eligible
        deductions are higher. This calculator lets you compare either approach by changing
        the deduction type.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <p class="last-updated">Last updated: April 2026</p>
</section>

  <footer>
    <a href="/privacy-policy">Privacy Policy</a>
    <a href="/terms">Terms</a>
    <a href="/disclaimer">Disclaimer</a>
    <a href="/contact">Contact</a>
    <p>© 2026 MyTaxCalcs.com</p>
  </footer>
</body>
</html>

